00:00:05.440 --> 00:00:09.130
define the variable, age, and I'm going to use my age in

00:00:09.130 --> 00:00:13.340
spirit, which is 7. And then, we'll multiply that by the

00:00:13.340 --> 00:00:15.960
number of days in a year. But let's also define

00:00:15.960 --> 00:00:18.960
a variable for the number of days in a year. And

00:00:18.960 --> 00:00:22.510
we could use 365. If we want to account for leap years,

00:00:22.510 --> 00:00:26.360
it would be more accurate to use 365 and a quarter,

00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:28.480
since one quarter of the years are leap years.

00:00:29.660 --> 00:00:32.460
And to compute the number of days that I've been

00:00:32.460 --> 00:00:35.360
alive, we can multiply those two values and print

00:00:35.360 --> 00:00:38.540
out the result. So let's try that in the Python

00:00:38.540 --> 00:00:41.600
interpreter. So here, we've defined our two variables. We

00:00:41.600 --> 00:00:44.890
have age is 7, not my real age, in case

00:00:44.890 --> 00:00:49.100
you're wondering. And days_in_year is 365 and a quarter.

00:00:49.100 --> 00:00:51.430
So we'll multiply those two to print out the result,

00:00:51.430 --> 00:00:56.160
which is 2556 and 3 quarter days. Quest to do

00:00:56.160 --> 00:00:58.990
